title: Former IU star Troy Williams wins D-League dunk contest
text:
Former IU star Troy Williams wins D-League dunk contest Jim Ayello , jim.ayello@indystar.com Published 4:17 p.m. ET Feb. 18, 2017 | Updated 43 minutes ago Dec 13, 2016; Cleveland, OH, USA; Memphis Grizzlies forward Troy Williams (10) dunks against the Cleveland Cavaliers in the third quarter at Quicken Loans Arena. (Photo: David Richard-USA TODAY Sports) 3 CONNECT COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Former IU star Troy Williams was crowned dunk champion of the NBA Developmental League on Saturday during All-Star weekend in New Orleans. 
Williams, who plays for Memphis Grizzlies affiliate Iowa Energy, scored a perfect 50 on his semifinal dunk to advance to the final. Indiana fared well in 3-point contest as well with Marion High School graduate Scott Wood took home the top prize. 
Wood plays for Golden State Warriors affiliate, the Santa Cruz Warriors. The champ is here! @scottwood15 was MONEY from beyond the arc to win the #DLeague3Point Contest! pic.twitter.com/eUZOWnggEb ‚Äî NBA D-League (@nbadleague) February 18, 2017 
The state of Indiana will go for the dunk contest sweep at 8 tonight when Gary native and Pacers forward Glenn Robinson III participates in the NBA competition.
